Infinity Test – set-up schematic

The Infinity Test is performed on a flat rectangular area using the athlete’s own manual wheelchair:

  1. Place two cones 10 m apart along the long axis of the area.
  2. Overall width ≈ 3 m; ensure ≥ 10 m clearance above and below the path.
  3. The athlete follows a continuous “figure-eight” path between the cones.
  4. Measure the lap distance of the full ∞ loop (e.g., 24.4 m).
  5. Record the total number of laps in 3 min and compute mean laps·min⁻¹.

Official schematic from the Infinity Test protocol.

Model: VO₂∞ (mL·min⁻¹) = 461 × laps·min⁻¹ (95% CI: 405–517). VO₂Ergo ≈ 0.92 × VO₂∞ + 134; 1 W ≈ 5.9 mL·min⁻¹ O₂.
This tool is intended for research, clinical and performance applications in manual wheelchair users.
